{
  "texts": [
    "LLMs learned to distinguish between reliable and unreliable sources more effectively, by continuously challenging with contradictory information [26].",
    "Addressing Gaps in the LiteratureDespite the significant progress made in improving the factual accuracy of LLMs and the development of RAG systems, several gaps in the literature remain.",
    "One notable gap is the lack of comprehensive studies on the integration of reverse proxystyle RAG with LLMs, particularly in the context of open-source models like Llama.",
    "While previous research has demonstrated the potential of RAG to enhance factual accuracy, the specific implementation details and architectural considerations for reverse proxy-style integration have not been extensively explored.",
    "Furthermore, existing studies have primarily focused on commercial LLMs, leaving a gap in understanding the applicability and effectiveness of RAG in open-source models."
  ]
}